<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="41" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1216,1485]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1219,1245]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<specimenCount box="[288,308,1219,1239]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
. Size small. Fore tibiae with ventral spines arranged in 
<typeStatus box="[981,1031,1219,1245]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">type</typeStatus>
4, 5 (1, 1). Median process of 9 
<superScript attach="none" box="[1423,1435,1216,1230]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">th</superScript>
abdominal tergite very long and symmetrical, with dilated apex into sharped lateral angle (
<figureCitation box="[1214,1293,1259,1285]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–13" captionStartId="5.[151,269,748,772]" captionTargetBox="[234,1364,181,713]" captionTargetId="figure-127@5.[151,1436,180,739]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11–13. Alloxiphidiopsis longicauda sp. n. 11, male abdominal end, dorsal view; 12, male abdominal end, lateral view; 13, male abdominal end, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097467" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097467/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Fig.11</figureCitation>
). Hind margin of last abdominal tergite with two short lobes. Cerci long and asymmetrical, left cercus distinctly longer than right one (
<figureCitation box="[330,410,1339,1365]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–13" captionStartId="5.[151,269,748,772]" captionTargetBox="[234,1364,181,713]" captionTargetId="figure-127@5.[151,1436,180,739]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11–13. Alloxiphidiopsis longicauda sp. n. 11, male abdominal end, dorsal view; 12, male abdominal end, lateral view; 13, male abdominal end, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097467" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097467/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Fig.13</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1216,1485]" box="[198,349,1379,1405]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">
<specimenCount box="[198,218,1379,1399]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
. unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1216,1485]" box="[198,950,1419,1445]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,343,1419,1445]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Coloration:</emphasis>
Yellowish (living possibly greenish), unicolourous.
</paragraph>
