<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1715,1947]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1795,1821]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Discussion.</emphasis>
The males of this new species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bey-Bienko, 1962)" authorityName="Liu &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Bey-Bienko" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[920,1323,1795,1821]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Alloxiphidiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irregularis">
<emphasis box="[920,1080,1795,1820]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">A. irregularis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bey-Bienko, GJ" box="[1096,1315,1795,1821]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41" pagination="110 - 138" refId="ref2500" refString="Bey-Bienko, GJ. (1962) Results of the Chinese - Soviet Zoologicalbotanical expeditions to South-Western China 1955 - 1957. New or less-known Tettigonioidea (Orthoptera) from Szechuan and Yunnan. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute, USSR Academy of Sciences, Leningrad, 30, 110 - 138." type="journal article" year="1962">Bey-Bienko, 1962</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in the shape of 9 
<superScript attach="left" box="[396,408,1835,1849]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">th</superScript>
abdominal tergite and left cercus distinctly longer than right one.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
